[INST]
What is the origin of standard gauge for railways?
[/INST]

<<SYS>>
The standard gauge is a unit of length used to measure the distance between two points on a railway track. The standard gauge was originally set at 4 ft 8+1⁄2 in (1,435 mm) by British engineers in the early 19th century as a way to ensure that all railways would have tracks of similar size and dimensions for easy interchange between them.
[/SYS]
